{
  "document_id": "job-28",
  "title": "Job 28",
  "type": "scripture",
  "translation": "NRSVue",
  "blocks": [
    {
      "block_id": "job-28-1",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 1,
      "text": "“Surely there is a mine for silver"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-28-2",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 2,
      "text": "Iron is taken out of the earth,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-28-3",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 3,
      "text": "Miners put an end to darkness"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-28-4",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 4,
      "text": "They open shafts in a valley away from human habitation;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-28-5",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 5,
      "text": "As for the earth, out of it comes bread,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-28-6",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 6,
      "text": "Its stones are the place of sapphires,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-28-7",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 7,
      "text": "“That path no bird of prey knows,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-28-8",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 8,
      "text": "The proud wild animals have not trodden it;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-28-9",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 9,
      "text": "“They put their hand to the flinty rock"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-28-10",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 10,
      "text": "They cut out channels in the rocks,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-28-11",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 11,
      "text": "The sources of the rivers they probe;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-28-12",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 12,
      "text": "“But where shall wisdom be found?"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-28-13",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 13,
      "text": "Mortals do not know the way to it,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-28-14",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 14,
      "text": "The deep says, ‘It is not in me,’"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-28-15",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 15,
      "text": "It cannot be gotten for gold,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-28-16",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 16,
      "text": "It cannot be valued in the gold of Ophir,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-28-17",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 17,
      "text": "Gold and glass cannot equal it,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-28-18",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 18,
      "text": "No mention shall be made of coral or of crystal;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-28-19",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 19,
      "text": "The chrysolite of Cush cannot compare with it,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-28-20",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 20,
      "text": "“Where then does wisdom come from?"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-28-21",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 21,
      "text": "It is hidden from the eyes of all living"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-28-22",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 22,
      "text": "Abaddon and Death say,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-28-23",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 23,
      "text": "“God understands the way to it,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-28-24",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 24,
      "text": "For he looks to the ends of the earth"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-28-25",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 25,
      "text": "When he gave to the wind its weight"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-28-26",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 26,
      "text": "when he made a decree for the rain,"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-28-27",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 27,
      "text": "then he saw it and declared it;"
    },
    {
      "block_id": "job-28-28",
      "type": "verse",
      "number": 28,
      "text": "And he said to humankind,"
    }
  ]
}